<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id7a475459-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0" identifier="/us/usc/t15/s4808"><num value="4808">§ 4808.</num><heading> Authorization of appropriations</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">There are authorized to be appropriated for each of the fiscal years 1991 and 1992 such sums as may be necessary not to exceed $5,000,000 to carry out the provisions of this chapter.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id7a47545a-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0">(<ref href="/us/pl/100/418/tV/s5209">Pub. L. 100–418, title V, § 5209</ref>, <date date="1988-08-23">Aug. 23, 1988</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/102/1461">102 Stat. 1461</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/101/382/tI/s133/e">Pub. L. 101–382, title I, § 133(e)</ref>, <date date="1990-08-20">Aug. 20, 1990</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/104/649">104 Stat. 649</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
